<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>cut someone dead • cut someone’s throat</xh5><p> <i>cut someone dead—</i>1. refuse to recognize a person; pretend not to know smb.: She proceeded on her way, her nose at a celebrated elevation—an icy nose. She <u>cut him dead</u>. 2. ignore a person when being talked to (because one is angry, etc.): He started talking to her and she <u>cut him dead</u> saying “I don’t want to hear your life history, pal!”</p><p> <i>cut someone’s throat</i>—(hyperbolic) cause smb.’s ruin or downfall: We’re shorthanded right now, and Genevieve would <u>cut my throat</u> if I tried to send you.</p> </entry>
